HEADWORD: piton
<hw>pi"ton</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"t⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mountain
Climbing)</fld> <def>A metal spike having a sharpened point on one end,
and a hole through which a rope can be passed on the other; it is driven
into the face of a rock cliff during climbing, and used as an anchor
point for a rope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitot's tube</ent>⟦br⟧
